# Component Standards

## Required File Structure

Each component must have these files:

- `ComponentName.tsx` - Main implementation
- `ComponentName.types.ts` - Type definitions
- `ComponentName.styles.ts` - Styles with CVA
- `ComponentName.test.tsx` - Unit tests
- `ComponentName.stories.tsx` - Storybook stories
- `index.ts` - Exports

## File Generation Rules

**CRITICAL**: Do NOT generate example files (`.example.tsx`, `.example.ts`, etc.).

- **Use Storybook stories instead**: All examples and demonstrations should be in `ComponentName.stories.tsx`
- **Stories are the documentation**: Storybook stories serve as both examples and interactive documentation
- **No separate example files**: Avoid creating `ComponentName.example.tsx` or similar files
- **Keep examples in stories**: All usage examples, variants, and demonstrations belong in the stories file

## Naming Conventions

- **PascalCase** for component names: `Button`, `Input`, `Modal`
- **camelCase** for props: `$isLoading`, `$fullWidth`, `$ariaLabel`
- **CRITICAL**: All custom props MUST use the `$` prefix to avoid conflicts with native HTML attributes

## Component Hierarchy (Atomic Design)

- **Atoms**: Basic components, no dependencies, highly reusable
- **Molecules**: Combine 2-3 atoms for specific functionality
- **Organisms**: Complex components that combine multiple molecules and atoms
- **Patterns**: Reusable patterns that combine multiple organisms

## Class Variance Authority (CVA) Usage

All components MUST use CVA for type-safe variant management with Tailwind CSS v4 and design tokens:

```typescript
import { cva } from 'class-variance-authority';

export const componentVariants = cva(
  // Base styles using design tokens
  [
    'typo-body-2-emphasized whitespace-nowrap rounded-x2',
    'flex items-center justify-center w-fit',
    'disabled:pointer-events-none disabled:cursor-not-allowed',
    'relative overflow-hidden focus-visible:!outline-[2px] focus-visible:!outline-offset-2 focus-visible:!outline-stroke-brand',
  ],
  {
    variants: {
      $variant: {
        primary: [
          'bg-background-brand !text-text-and-icons-always-white',
          'border-background-brand',
          'hover:bg-linear-brand active:bg-linear-pressed-brand focus-visible:bg-linear-brand',
          'disabled:disabled-button-brand',
        ],
        secondary: [
          'bg-background-secondary text-text-and-icons-primary',
          'border-stroke-secondary',
          'hover:bg-background-tertiary active:bg-background-tertiary focus-visible:bg-background-tertiary',
        ],
        destructive: [
          'bg-background-danger !text-text-and-icons-always-white',
          'border-background-danger',
          'hover:bg-linear-destructive active:bg-linear-pressed-destructive focus-visible:bg-linear-destructive',
          'disabled:disabled-button-destructive',
        ],
      },
      $size: {
        sm: 'px-x3 py-x2 text-typo-body-3 min-h-[32px]',
        md: 'px-x4 py-x3 text-typo-body-2 min-h-[40px]',
        lg: 'px-x6 py-x4 text-typo-body-1 min-h-[48px]',
      },
    },
    defaultVariants: {
      $variant: 'primary',
      $size: 'md',
    },
  },
);
```

## Design Tokens (PRIORITY)

**CRITICAL**: ALWAYS use design tokens from `/packages/react/src/styles/` instead of hardcoded values. This is the highest priority for maintaining consistency and brand identity.

### Token Structure in packages/react/styles/

```
packages/react/src/styles/
├── tokens/                   # Design tokens
│   ├── colors.css           # Color tokens
│   ├── spacings.css         # Spacing tokens
│   ├── font-sizes.css       # Typography tokens
│   ├── radius.css           # Border radius tokens
│   └── shadows.css          # Shadow tokens
├── utility/                 # Utility classes
│   ├── typography.css       # Typography utilities
│   ├── elevation.css        # Shadow utilities
│   └── button.css           # Component utilities
└── fonts/                   # Font files
    └── inter/               # Inter font family
```

### Color Tokens (PRIORITY)

**ALWAYS** use predefined color tokens from the design system:

```typescript
// ✅ Correct - using design system colors
'bg-background-brand text-text-and-icons-always-white';
'bg-background-danger text-text-and-icons-always-white';
'bg-background-success text-text-and-icons-always-white';
'text-text-and-icons-primary';
'text-text-and-icons-secondary';
'border-stroke-brand';
'border-stroke-secondary';

// ❌ Wrong - hardcoded colors
'bg-blue-500 text-white';
'bg-red-500 text-white';
'bg-green-500 text-white';
'text-gray-900';
'text-gray-600';
'border-blue-500';
```

### Spacing Tokens (PRIORITY)

**ALWAYS** use spacing tokens for consistent spacing:

```typescript
// ✅ Correct - using spacing tokens
'px-x4 py-x3'; // 16px horizontal, 12px vertical
'mx-x2 my-x1'; // 8px horizontal, 4px vertical
'gap-x3'; // 12px gap
'p-x4 m-x2'; // 16px padding, 8px margin

// ❌ Wrong - hardcoded spacing
'px-4 py-3'; // Use px-x4 py-x3 instead
'mx-2 my-1'; // Use mx-x2 my-x1 instead
'gap-3'; // Use gap-x3 instead
'p-4 m-2'; // Use p-x4 m-x2 instead
```

### Typography Tokens (PRIORITY)

**ALWAYS** use typography utilities from the design system:

```typescript
// ✅ Correct - using typography utilities
'typo-headline-1'; // Headline 1 with proper font features
'typo-headline-2'; // Headline 2 with proper font features
'typo-headline-3'; // Headline 3 with proper font features
'typo-body-1'; // Body 1 text
'typo-body-2'; // Body 2 text
'typo-body-2-emphasized'; // Body 2 with emphasis
'typo-meta'; // Meta text
'typo-amount'; // Amount/currency text

// ❌ Wrong - manual typography
'text-2xl font-bold'; // Use typo-headline-1 instead
'text-xl font-semibold'; // Use typo-headline-2 instead
'text-lg font-medium'; // Use typo-headline-3 instead
'text-base'; // Use typo-body-1 instead
'text-sm font-medium'; // Use typo-body-2-emphasized instead
```

### Radius Tokens (PRIORITY)

**ALWAYS** use radius tokens for consistent border radius:

```typescript
// ✅ Correct - using radius tokens
'rounded-x2'; // 8px border radius
'rounded-x4'; // 16px border radius
'rounded-t-x2'; // 8px top border radius

// ❌ Wrong - hardcoded radius
'rounded-md'; // Use rounded-x2 instead
'rounded-lg'; // Use rounded-x4 instead
'rounded-t-md'; // Use rounded-t-x2 instead
```

### Shadow Tokens (PRIORITY)

**ALWAYS** use shadow tokens for consistent elevation:

```typescript
// ✅ Correct - using shadow tokens
'shadow-s3'; // Very light shadow
'shadow-s8'; // Medium shadow
'shadow-s15'; // Strong shadow

// ❌ Wrong - hardcoded shadows
'shadow-sm'; // Use shadow-s3 instead
'shadow-md'; // Use shadow-s8 instead
'shadow-lg'; // Use shadow-s15 instead
```

### Font Tokens (PRIORITY)

**ALWAYS** use font utilities from the design system:

```typescript
// ✅ Correct - using font utilities
'font-inter'; // Inter font family
'font-weight-bold'; // Bold weight
'font-weight-medium'; // Medium weight
'font-weight-regular'; // Regular weight

// ❌ Wrong - hardcoded fonts
'font-sans'; // Use font-inter instead
'font-bold'; // Use font-weight-bold instead
'font-medium'; // Use font-weight-medium instead
```

### Utility Classes (PRIORITY)

**ALWAYS** use utility classes from `/packages/react/src/styles/utility/`:

```typescript
// ✅ Correct - using utility classes
'elevation-s3'; // Light elevation
'elevation-s8'; // Medium elevation
'elevation-s15'; // Strong elevation
'button-primary'; // Primary button styles
'button-secondary'; // Secondary button styles

// ❌ Wrong - manual utilities
'shadow-sm'; // Use elevation-s3 instead
'shadow-md'; // Use elevation-s8 instead
'shadow-lg'; // Use elevation-s15 instead
```

### Component Implementation

```typescript
// ✅ Good - using all design tokens correctly
const Button = ({ $variant, $size, children }: ButtonProps) => {
  return (
    <button
      className={cn(
        // Typography from design system
        'typo-body-2-emphasized',
        // Spacing from design system
        'px-x4 py-x3',
        // Radius from design system
        'rounded-x2',
        // Colors from design system
        $variant === 'primary'
          ? 'bg-background-brand text-text-and-icons-always-white'
          : 'bg-background-secondary text-text-and-icons-primary',
        // Shadows from design system
        'shadow-s3'
      )}
    >
      {children}
    </button>
  );
};
```

## Accessibility

### WCAG 2.1 AA Compliance

- Each component must be WCAG 2.1 AA compliant
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Implement appropriate ARIA attributes
- Support keyboard navigation
- Support screen readers

### Color Contrast Guidelines (PRIORITY)

**CRITICAL**: Do NOT automatically change colors for contrast compliance. Instead:

1. **Use design tokens ONLY**: Always use predefined color tokens from `/packages/react/src/styles/tokens/colors.css`
2. **Pre-approved combinations**: Use only color combinations that have been pre-tested for WCAG 2.1 AA compliance
3. **Design system validation**: Ensure all color combinations in the design system meet contrast requirements
4. **Manual override only**: If contrast issues arise, work with the design team to create new approved color combinations

```typescript
// ✅ Good - using approved design tokens from packages/react/src/styles/
const Button = ({ $variant }: ButtonProps) => {
  return (
    <button
      className={cn(
        // Using design system color tokens (PRIORITY)
        'bg-background-brand text-text-and-icons-always-white', // Pre-approved combination
        'hover:bg-linear-brand focus-visible:bg-linear-brand',
        // Using design system focus tokens
        'focus-visible:!outline-[2px] focus-visible:!outline-offset-2 focus-visible:!outline-stroke-brand'
      )}
    >
      {children}
    </button>
  );
};

// ❌ Bad - automatic color changes or hardcoded colors
const Button = ({ $variant, $contrastMode }: ButtonProps) => {
  const backgroundColor = $contrastMode === 'high' ? '#000000' : '#0069f1'; // Don't do this
  return <button style={{ backgroundColor }}>{children}</button>;
};

// ❌ Bad - hardcoded colors instead of design tokens
const Button = ({ $variant }: ButtonProps) => {
  return (
    <button className="bg-blue-500 text-white"> {/* Don't do this */}
      {children}
    </button>
  );
};
```

### Proactive Contrast Management (PRIORITY)

Instead of reactive color changes, implement proactive solutions using design tokens:

```typescript
// ✅ Good - using semantic color tokens from design system that are pre-tested
const Alert = ({ $variant, children }: AlertProps) => {
  return (
    <div
      className={cn(
        // Using design system spacing and radius tokens
        'p-x4 rounded-x2 border',
        {
          // Using design system color tokens (PRIORITY)
          'bg-background-success text-text-and-icons-always-white border-stroke-success': $variant === 'success',
          'bg-background-danger text-text-and-icons-always-white border-stroke-danger': $variant === 'error',
          'bg-background-warning text-text-and-icons-primary border-stroke-warning': $variant === 'warning',
        }
      )}
    >
      {children}
    </div>
  );
};

// ✅ Good - using focus states with design tokens that meet contrast requirements
const Input = ({ $error, ...props }: InputProps) => {
  return (
    <input
      className={cn(
        // Using design system spacing and radius tokens
        'px-x4 py-x3 rounded-x2 border',
        // Using design system focus tokens (PRIORITY)
        'focus-visible:!outline-[2px] focus-visible:!outline-offset-2 focus-visible:!outline-stroke-brand',
        $error
          ? 'border-stroke-danger focus-visible:!outline-stroke-danger'
          : 'border-stroke-secondary focus-visible:!outline-stroke-brand'
      )}
      {...props}
    />
  );
};

// ✅ Good - using design system typography tokens for accessibility
const Label = ({ children, $required }: LabelProps) => {
  return (
    <label
      className={cn(
        // Using design system typography tokens (PRIORITY)
        'typo-body-2-emphasized text-text-and-icons-primary',
        // Using design system spacing tokens
        'block mb-x2'
      )}
    >
      {children}
      {$required && (
        <span className="text-text-and-icons-danger ml-x1" aria-label="required">
          *
        </span>
      )}
    </label>
  );
};
```

### Design System Color Validation (PRIORITY)

1. **Pre-validate all combinations**: Ensure all color combinations in `/packages/react/src/styles/tokens/colors.css` meet WCAG 2.1 AA requirements
2. **Document approved combinations**: Maintain a list of approved color combinations from the design system
3. **Automated testing**: Use tools like `@storybook/addon-a11y` to validate contrast ratios of design tokens
4. **Design review**: Include accessibility review in the design process for all new design tokens
5. **Token validation**: Validate all new color tokens against WCAG 2.1 AA before adding to the design system

### Accessibility Testing (PRIORITY)

- Test with screen readers (NVDA, JAWS, VoiceOver)
- Test keyboard navigation (Tab, Enter, Escape, Arrow keys)
- Test with high contrast mode
- Validate ARIA attributes
- Test with zoom up to 200%
- Use automated tools like `axe-core` for contrast validation
- **Test design tokens**: Validate all color combinations from `/packages/react/src/styles/tokens/colors.css`
- **Token accessibility**: Ensure all design tokens meet WCAG 2.1 AA requirements
- **Component testing**: Test components using only design system tokens for accessibility compliance
